Program: Omnibus
Title: The Letters of Charles Dickens
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376kjz
Last Broadcast Date: 29 March 1993
A look at the latest volume of Charles Dickens letters to be published. They cover the years 1853-1855, ending when he was 43. The programme includes readings from the letters and an interview with editor Professor Kathleen Tillotson.